    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Removal</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s07.2">
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, read all safety instructions in the "Safety Information"
                        section of this manual.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, shift the transmission to park or neutral, set the
                        parking brake, and block the wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine has cooled before removing
                        components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, remove the ground cable from the negative terminal of the
                        main battery before disconnecting or connecting electrical components. Always connect the ground
                        cable last.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not let engine fluids stay on your skin. Clean skin
                        and nails using hand cleaner and wash with soap and water. Wash or discard clothing and rags
                        contaminated with engine fluids.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <regulation>
                    <para>Engine fluids (oil, fuel, and coolant) may be a threat to the environment. Recycle or dispose
                        of engine fluids according to applicable regulations. Never put engine fluids in the trash, on
                        the ground, in sewers or bodies of water.
                    </para>
                </regulation>
                <regulation>
                    <para>Dispose of fuel according to applicable regulations in a correct container clearly marked
                        DIESEL FUEL.
                    </para>
                </regulation>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to the following service sections for information on removal of components prior to this
                        section.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Engine Electrical</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Exhaust Gas Recirculating (EGR) System</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT)</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Air Compressor and Power Steering/Fuel Pump</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc id="s07.2.1" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Fuel Prescreen Element</title>
            <figure id="f3450007007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM11/M11123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removal of prescreen element</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Gear driven fuel pump assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Prescreen bowl</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, dispose of fuel in a container marked DIESEL FUEL,
                        according to applicable regulations.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a suitable container under prescreen bowl to catch draining fuel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a 30 mm box end wrench to remove prescreen bowl from power steering/fuel pump.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean prescreen element after inspection, or replace if damaged.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
